evision-awards-2017-mary-berry-triumphs-casualty/ |title=National Television Awards 2017: Mary Berry triumphs and Casualty wins over Game of Thrones, plus full list of winners|author=Press Association |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=26 January 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[2017 British Academy Television Awards|BAFTA]]\n| Features\n| ''The Great British Bake Off'' production team\n| align=\"center\" {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-39563665 |title=Bafta TV Awards 2017: All the winners and nominees |date= 14 May 2017 |work=BBC }}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Asian Viewers Television Awards]]\n|Best Of British\n| ''The Great British Bake Off''\n|{{nom}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2019\n| [[24th National Television Awards|National Television Award]]\n| Factual Entertainment\n| ''The Great British Bake Off''\n| align=\"center\" {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-46782619|title=Ant and Dec shortlisted for National Television Awards|date=7 January 2019|work=BBC}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[2019 British Academy Television Awards|BAFTA]]\n| Features\n| ''The Great British Bake Off''\n| align=\"center\" {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-47731024 |title= Bafta TV Awards 2019: Full winners and nominees list |date=12 May 2019 |work=BBC}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2020\n| [[25th National Television Awards|National Television Award]]\n| Challenge Show\n| ''The Great British Bake Off''\n| align=\"center\" {{won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=nta />\n|-\n|}\n\n== International broadcast and versions ==\nThe UK version of ''The Great British Bake Off'' is broadcast in many countries and it has been sold to 196 territories as of 2015.<ref>{{cite news |url= https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2015/jul/28/great-british-bake-off-contestants-series-six |title=Great British Bake Off: new contestants poised to serve up sixth series |author=John Plunkett |date=28 July 2015 |work=The Guardian }}</ref> The format has also been sold to 20 territories by 2015, making it the third most successful BBC format after ''[[Dancing with the Stars]]'' (''[[Strictly Come Dancing]]'') and ''[[The Weakest Link]]''.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2015/aug/04/great-british-bake-off-recipe-sweet-success-bbc-worldwide |title=Great British Bake Off recipe has proved a sweet success for BBC Worldwide |author= Tara Conlan|date= 4 August 2015 |work=Guardian}}</ref> Many of these shows have been successful.<ref name=\"ensor\">{{cite news |url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/tvandradio/9844086/The-Great-British-Bake-Off-proves-it-has-the-recipe-for-success-as-show-goes-global.html|title = The Great British Bake Off proves it has the recipe for success as show goes global|author = Josie Ensor|date = 3 February 2013|work = Daily Telegraph}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2012/oct/12/great-british-bake-off-round-the-world |title=The Great British Bake Off goes global: from Sweden to Australia the show is flourishing |author=Mark Cook|date= 12 October 2012 |work=The Guardian }}</ref> The ''[[Junior Bake Off]]'' format has also been sold to Thailand.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/worldwide/2014/junior-bake-off-thailand |title=BBC Worldwide sells very first Junior Bake Off format to Thailand|date=21 July 2014 |work =BBC }}</ref>\n\nBeginning in 2014, the US broadcaster [[Public Broadcasting Service|PBS]] has aired five series of the show under the name ''The Great British Baking Show''.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Diamond|first1=Kerry|title=Finally! 'The Great British Bake Off' Has Arrived in America|url=https://www.yahoo.com/food/anglophiles-and-baking-enthusiasts-received-a-106546370621.html|website=Yahoo! Food|accessdate=11 January 2015}}</ref> The change of name was necessary due to the fact that \"Bake-Off\" is a registered trademark of [[Pillsbury Bake-Off|Pillsbury]] in the United States.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sikka |first1=Madhulika |title=What's in a Name? |url=http://www.pbs.org/publiceditor/blogs/pbs-public-editor/whats-in-a-name/ |website=pbs.org |accessdate=29 November 2018 |date=12 Oct 2017}}</ref>  The fifth British series was broadcast as Season 1 in Winter 2014\u20132015;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pbs.org/food/features/great-british-baking-show-episodes/|title=The Great British Baking Show: Season 1 Episodes \u2013 PBS Food|date=22 December 2014|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2016}}</ref> the fourth series was then broadcast as Season 2 in Fall 2015,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pbs.org/food/features/great-british-baking-show-season-2-episodes/|title=Season 2 Episodes \u2013 Great British Baking Show \u2013 PBS Food|date=17 August 2015|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2016}}</ref> the sixth series was broadcast as Season 3 in Summer 2016, and the seventh series was broadcast as Season 4 in Summer 2017. After the show moved to Channel 4, PBS purchased the BBC's third series, broadcasting it as Season 5 instead of licensing the eighth series from Channel 4. As of 2018, PBS has the rights to air the second BBC series as Season 6 in 2019, and has chosen to not license the Channel 4 series.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/think/opinion/pbs-great-british-baking-show-premiere-marred-behind-scenes-drama-ncna886111|title=PBS' \"Great British Baking Show\" premiere marred by behind-the-scenes drama. And U.S. audiences will pay the price. By Ani Bundel|date=24 June 2018|publisher=NBC News|accessdate=24 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n[[CBC Television]] began broadcasting ''The Great British Bake Off'' in Canada in August 2016, starting with the sixth series and also with the ''Great British Baking Show'' title. Subsequent seasons have aired the summer following their British airings, with Series 9 debuting in July 2019.<ref>{{cite news|title=How to Watch The Great British Baking Show in Canada|url=http://www.cbc.ca/life/the-great-british-baking-show/how-to-watch-the-great-british-baking-show-in-canada-1.4180368|website=CBC|accessdate=30 August 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, the Channel 4 Series 8 was made available in the United States on [[Netflix]] as \"Collection 5\" and a \"Netflix original production\" alongside the four series previously broadcast on PBS. In addition, Netflix added ''The Great British Baking Show: The Beginnings'' which features the British series 3.\n\n=== International versions ===\nCurrent and upcoming versions include:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.c21media.net/archives/77478 |title=Europe whips up Bake Off adaptations |publisher=c21media.net |date=29 February 2012 |accessdate=7 October 2012}}</ref>\n\n'''Legend:'''\n{{Color box|#92FF8D|border=darkgray}} Airing or in production &nbsp;\n{{Color box|#FF7777|border=darkgray}} No longer airing &nbsp;\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:left; line-height:16px; background:#f8f8ff; width:100%;\"\n|-\n! Country !! Local title !! Host(s) !! Judges !! Channel !! Premiere\n|-\n| style=\"background:#f77;\"|{{Flagcountry|Argentina}} || ''[[Bake Off Argentina, El Gran Pastelero]]''<br />(''Bake Off Argentina, The Great Baker'') || [[Paula Chaves]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://television.com.ar/bake-off-argentina-el-gran-pastelero-se-llamara-la-adaptacion-de-telefe-del-formato-britanico/72951|title=Bake Off Argentina, El Gran Pastelero se llamar\u00e1 la adaptaci\u00f3n de telefe del formato brit\u00e1nico (Spanish)|author=Television.com.ar|work=[[television.com.ar]]|date=20 January 2018}}</ref> || Christophe Krywonis<br />Dami\u00e1n Petular<br />Pamela Villar || [[Telefe]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://telefe.com/convocatorias/participa-en-telefe/convocatoria-se-viene-la-competencia-para-pasteleros-amateurs/|title=\u00a1Llega Bake off! La competencia para pasteleros amateurs (Spanish)|author=Telefe|publisher=telefe.com|date=20 January 2018}}</ref> || 8